Mixing.Description: GO was dispersed into THF to get a homogeneous colloid

ChooseParameter.Other: The substance was placed in a  three-necked flask equipped with a nitrogen inlet, a mechanical stirrer, a dropping funnel and an ice-bath

Mixing.Description: TEA was added and mechanically stirred into the mixture.
HCTP dissolved in THF was slowly dropped into the flask for 2 hrs while stirring
The mixture was then mechanically stirred under a nitrogen gas atmosphere

ChooseParameter.Other: Glycidol dissolved in THF was dropped into reactor in 0.5 hrs.

Mixing.Description: The reaction continued overnight while mechanical stirring at ambient temperature.

ChooseParameter.Other: The obtained mixture was then washed with deionized water and THF.

Cooling.Description: 115 mL of H2SO4 was placed in a four-necked flask and cooled in an ice bath

ChooseParameter.Other: 2.5 g NaNO3 and 5.0 g expandable graphite were added to the cooled mixture.

Mixing.Description: The mixture was stirred at a temperature below 5 C

ChooseParameter.Other: 35.0 g KMnO4 was slowly added into the mixture

Mixing.Description: Mixture was stirred at a temperature below 10 C

Heating.Description: The mixture was heated and maintained at 35 C for 60 mins.

Mixing.Description: 230 mL H2O was added dropwisely to the mixture w/ strong mechanical stirring. The temperature was controlled below 98 C via a water bath

ChooseParameter.Other: The mud was diluted with 1000 mL deionized water
30% H2O2 was dripped into the mud to reduce the unreacted KMnO4 until the slurry turned golden yellow.
Resultant was washed with dilute hydrochloric acid, hot deionized water and THF.

Filler.Description: FGO was prepared from GO by surface modification with HCTP

Mixing.Description: FGO was dispersed in THF and added into EPR.
The EPR and  FGO mixture was mechanically stirred

Heating.Description: The mixture was placed in a vacuum oven overnight

Mixing.Description: DDM was added to the mixture by blending.

Heating.Description: The mixture was poured into a mold and pre-cured in an oven.
Subsequently, the mixture was post cured
